               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dāwit “Psalter” (fols. 1r-142vb)
 I-1) Mazmura Dāwit “Psalms of
                     David” (fols. 1r–109v, fols. 120r–131v)
 I-2) Maḥālǝya nabiyāt “The
                     Canticles of the Prophets” (fols. 109v–119v, fols. 132r–132v), incomplete
                     I-3) Maḥālǝya maḥālǝy “Song of Songs” (fols. 132v–138v)
 I-4) Wǝddāse
                     Māryām “Praise of Mary” (fols. 138va-142vb), incomplete
 
 Additio
                     1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <locus from="1r" to="142vb"/>
                     <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
                     
                     <textLang mainLang="gez"/>
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1">
                        <locus from="1r" to="109v"/><locus from="120r" to="131v"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                        <note>- Traditional interpretation of the Hebrew letters (except for Aleph) in
                           Psalm 118 is missing.</note>
                        <note>- Psalm 85 is mistakenly numbered as 77 (<locus target="#61r">61r</locus>). P115, 116, 117
                           are mistakenly numbered as 114, 115, 116 respectively (<locus from="87r" to="88v">87r-88v</locus>). P124, 125 are
                           mistakenly numbered as 123, 124 respectively (<locus target="#96v">96v</locus>). P145 is mistakenly numbered
                           as 146 (<locus target="#107r">107r</locus>).</note>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2">
                        <locus from="109v" to="119v"/> <locus from="132r" to="132v"/>
                        <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
                        <note>- The First Prayer of Moses begins on <locus target="#109v">109v</locus> (Ex. 15:1-2a), then continues on <locus target="#118r">118r</locus>, 118v (Ex. 15:2b up to the end). 
                           On <locus target="#119v">119v</locus>, Text I-2 ends with the Prayer of Habakkuk; of the
                           following Prayer of Isaiah, only the heading is present. Another part of
                           the text is contained on <locus target="#132">132</locus>: the Prayer of Our
                           Lady Mary from Lk. 1:52 up to the end, the Prayer of Zechariah and the
                           Prayer of Simeon.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3">
                        <locus from="132v" to="138v"/>
                        <title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">Song of Songs</title>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4">
                        <locus from="138va" to="142vb"/>
                        <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse Māryām</title>
                     </msItem>
                     
                     
                  </msItem>
                  
