                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. is very worn. 
 The front board is
                           broken; the back board is missing.
 The Ms. has been resewn; only 2nd
                           and 3rd sewing stations has been used.
 The front board attachment is
                           almost totally destroyed.
 Many leaves are covered with dirt stains
                           and some are destroyed by rodents.
 Some folios are missing, some
                           folios are misplaced. 
 Not more than two fols. are missing between
                              <locus target="#119">119</locus> and 132 containing the Prayer of
                           Isaiah and the beginning of the Prayer of Our Lady Mary from Lk. 1:52.
                           
 The final part of Text I-4 is missing.
 The proper arrangement
                           of fols. is as follows: 1-2, 5-12, 3-4, 120-131, 13-119, 132-142. 
                           Some leaves are damaged, with portions of the text lost (e.g., <locus target="#104">104</locus>, 131, 142 etc.)
 Holes carefully amended
                           on <locus target="#12">12</locus>, 74.</condition>
